Program: Discovery
Title: Top Quark
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrw6z
Last Broadcast Date: 29 April 1994
What is a "top quark"? Have scientists at the Fermilab particle physics laboratory in Chicago really found a dozen examples? Also, using quantum mechanics in laser technology: Richard Dawkins responds to new research suggesting evolution happened faster than estimated. Presented by Roland Pease.